description: Josh Neufville's sublime strike helps promotion-chasing AFC Wimbledon to a League Two win over relegation-threatened Tranmere.
title: AFC Wimbledon 2-0 Tranmere Rovers
title_page: AFC Wimbledon 2-0 Tranmere Rovers - BBC Sport
maintext:
AFC Wimbledon have lost just one of their last five Football League games against Tranmere Rovers (W3 D1), and will be looking to record an EFL double over this opponent for the first time, after winning the reverse fixture 2-0 in November.
Tranmere Rovers have failed to win any of their three away Football League games against AFC Wimbledon (D2 L1), though theyâ€™ve also lost just two of their last 11 away league games in London since the start of the 2014-15 season (W5 D4).
AFC Wimbledon have won each of their last two league games and will be looking to win three in succession for the first time since September 2024.
Tranmere have lost each of their last six away league games in a row, last enduring a longer losing run on their travels between August and October 2023 (eight games).
